#: ../../D/Discordianism.rst:9
msgid ""
"The veneration of :ref:`Eris`\\, a.k.a. Discordia; widely popular among "
"hackers. Discordianism was popularized by Robert Shea and Robert Anton "
"Wilson's novel *Illuminatus!* as a sort of self-subverting Dada-Zen for "
"Westerners — it should on no account be taken seriously but is far more "
"serious than most jokes. Consider, for example, the Fifth Commandment of the"
" Pentabarf, from *Principia Discordia*\\: \"A Discordian is Prohibited of "
"Believing What he Reads.\" Discordianism is usually connected with an "
"elaborate conspiracy theory/joke involving millennia-long warfare between "
"the anarcho-surrealist partisans of Eris and a malevolent, authoritarian "
"secret society called the Illuminati. See :ref:`Religion<religion>` in "
"Appendix B, :ref:`Church-of-the-SubGenius`\\, and :ref:`ha-ha-only-"
"serious`\\."
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`Eris`\\ (別名Discordia)への崇拝。ハッカーの間で広く人気がある。DiscordianismはRobert "
"SheaとRobert Anton "
"Wilsonの小説『*Illuminatus!*』によって広まった。それは西洋人のための一種の自己破壊的なダダ的禅であり——決して真面目に受け取るべきではないが、たいていの冗談よりはるかに真剣である。たとえば、『*Principia"
" "
"Discordia*』にあるPentabarfの第五戒を考えてみよ。「Discordianは自分が読んだものを信じることを禁じられる。」Discordianismは通常、Erisのアナルコ・シュルレアリスム的パルチザンと、Illuminatiと呼ばれる悪意ある権威主義的秘密結社との間の数千年にわたる戦争を巡る、手の込んだ陰謀論/冗談と結びついている。付録Bの\\"
" :ref:`宗教<religion>`\\ 、\\ :ref:`Church-of-the-SubGenius`\\ 、\\ :ref:`ha-ha-"
"only-serious`\\ を参照。"
